<Project>

  <!--
    Shared-source manifest for the 'dotnet test' named-pipe protocol.

    PURPOSE
      The 'dotnet test' <-> Microsoft.Testing.Platform integration talks over a named pipe using a small, versioned
      binary protocol. This .props is the single canonical list of the source files that make up that protocol - the
      wire contract (serializer ids + field ids + handshake/session/state constants), the message models, the
      serializers, and the small serializer-registry + base infrastructure they need. The same files are compiled
      into Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the host side, via its default globbing) AND VENDORED (hand-copied) into the
      dotnet/sdk 'dotnet test' implementation (see its ObjectFieldIds.cs, which carries a "must be kept aligned with
      the testfx repo" warning), so the protocol has ONE source of truth instead of being duplicated by hand. Any
      drift is a silent wire-protocol break.

      testfx is the SOURCE OF TRUTH for these files. This .props is the canonical enumeration of the shared set:
      it lets the same source files be compiled into a standalone in-repo consumer (the contract test project) that
      guarantees they build independently, and it tells testfx contributors exactly which files dotnet/sdk vendors.
      dotnet/sdk tracks the same files in its eng/vendored-files.json manifest and a scheduled workflow opens an
      issue there whenever these upstream files change, so any change here may require a coordinated port in
      dotnet/sdk. See also dotnet/sdk eng/vendored-files.md.

    SCOPE
      Shared here:
        - Wire contract: IPC/ObjectFieldIds.cs, IPC/Constants.cs.
        - Interfaces + serializer registry: IPC/INamedPipeSerializer.cs, IPC/IRequest.cs, IPC/IResponse.cs,
          IPC/NamedPipeBase.cs (registry only).
        - Serializer infrastructure: IPC/Serializers/BaseSerializer.cs, NamedPipeSerializer.cs, RegisterSerializers.cs
          and the base request/response serializers (VoidResponse/TestHostCompletedRequest/TestHostProcessPIDRequest).
        - Message models + serializers for serializer ids 0-12 (Models/*.cs + Serializers/*.cs under this folder,
          plus the base models under IPC/Models/*.cs).

      Deliberately NOT shared (kept local to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, transport differs per repo):
        - The named-pipe transport: IPC/NamedPipeConnectionBase.cs (framing/buffers), IPC/NamedPipeServer.cs,
          IPC/NamedPipeClient.cs, IPC/IServer.cs, IPC/IClient.cs, IPC/PipeNameDescription.cs.
        - The host data consumer (DotnetTestDataConsumer.cs) and connection.

      The shared files are self-contained: BaseSerializer decouples from ApplicationStateGuard/RoslynDebug (it has its
      own Unreachable()/DebugAssert helpers); the DiscoveredTestMessage trait uses the platform-decoupled TraitMessage
      wire type instead of the public TestMetadataProperty; NamedPipeBase is registry-only (no PipeStream/framing). The
      infrastructure types are [Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.Embedded] so they are not exported by Microsoft.Testing.Platform
      and never conflict in a consumer that also references the platform. None of these changes alter the wire bytes
      (ids, field ids, order and layout are pinned by ObjectFieldIds.cs and the round-trip tests).

    USAGE
      Import this file from any project that needs the protocol source. Microsoft.Testing.Platform itself does NOT
      import it (it compiles these files via its default source globbing); importing it there would double-include them.
      The single canonical list of protocol files lives in the @(DotnetTestProtocolContractSource) item below;
      importing consumers (e.g. the standalone contract test project) get them as <Compile> items.
  -->
  <PropertyGroup>
    <_DotnetTestProtocolPlatform>$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)..\..</_DotnetTestProtocolPlatform>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <!-- Wire contract: serializer ids + field ids + handshake/session/state constants. -->
    <DotnetTestProtocolContractSource Include="$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)IPC\ObjectFieldIds.cs" />
    <DotnetTestProtocolContractSource Include="$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)IPC\Constants.cs" />

    <!-- Interfaces + serializer registry (platform IPC folder; transport files are intentionally excluded). -->
    <DotnetTestProtocolContractSource Include="$(_DotnetTestProtocolPlatform)\IPC\INamedPipeSerializer.cs" />
    <DotnetTestProtocolContractSource Include="$(_DotnetTestProtocolPlatform)\IPC\IRequest.cs" />
    <DotnetTestProtocolContractSource Include="$(_DotnetTestProtocolPlatform)\IPC\IResponse.cs" />
    <DotnetTestProtocolContractSource Include="$(_DotnetTestProtocolPlatform)\IPC\NamedPipeBase.cs" />

    <!-- Serializer infrastructure + base request/response serializers (all files in the platform IPC/Serializers folder).
         NOTE: this shares EVERY file in that folder; any new file dropped there is auto-exported into the SDK source
         share and must stay standalone-compilable (no dependency on the rest of Microsoft.Testing.Platform). -->
    <DotnetTestProtocolContractSource Include="$(_DotnetTestProtocolPlatform)\IPC\Serializers\*.cs" />

    <!-- Base request/response models (all files in the platform IPC/Models folder). Same "every file is shared" note as above. -->
    <DotnetTestProtocolContractSource Include="$(_DotnetTestProtocolPlatform)\IPC\Models\*.cs" />

    <!-- 'dotnet test' message models + serializers for serializer ids 0-12. -->
    <DotnetTestProtocolContractSource Include="$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)IPC\Models\*.cs" />
    <DotnetTestProtocolContractSource Include="$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)IPC\Serializers\*.cs" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <Compile Include="@(DotnetTestProtocolContractSource)" Link="DotnetTestProtocol\%(Filename)%(Extension)" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
